data.value:
Menu Buttons (View, Edit, Help) View: to change the appearance from dark to light. Edit : to cut, copy, or paste the displayed number. Help : to view About Calculator and Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
Basic operators (x, ÷ , +, -, =) x : multiplies the entered numbers. ÷ : divides the entered numbers. + : adds the entered numbers. - : subtracts the entered numbers. = : performs the operation.
Advanced Operators (√, %, 1/x, ±, .) √ (square root): gets the square root of a number. % (percent): depending on the used operator, it adds, subtracts, multiplies, or divides percentage to a number. Example: 12 + 8% = 12.96 1/x (reciprocal): gets the reciprocal of the displayed number. ± (positive/negative): changes the sign of a number to positive or negative. . (decimal): to use decimal numbers for high precision.
Memory Buttons (MS, MR, MC, M+, M-) MS (save): to store the currently displayed number for later use. MR (recall): to use the saved number. MC (clear): to clear the saved number. M+ (plus): to add the currently displayed number to the saved number. M- (minus): to subtract the currently displayed number to the saved number.
Other buttons (C, CE, Del) C (clear): to clear the display or reset the contents of the calculator CE (clear entry): to clear the currently entered number. Del (delete): to remove one digit from the displayed number.
